==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Panegyrist
<hw>Pan"e*gyr`ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>panegyrista</ets>, Gr. <grk>panhgyristh`s</grk>, one who attends a
<grk>panh`gyris</grk>: cf. <grk>panhgyri`zein</grk> to celebrate or
attend a public festival, to make a set speech, esp. a panegyric, in a
public assembly. See <er>Panegyric</er>.]</ety> <def>One who delivers a
panegyric; a eulogist; one who extols or praises, either by writing or
speaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If these <qex>panegyrists</qex> are in earnest.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Panegyrize</ent>⟦br⟧
